/*                                                                                    */
/**************************************************************************************/
/**************************************************************************************/


Writen by Byung Chul Yeo, Sang Soo Han in Korea Institute of Science of Technology

* autocal.sh: Calculate physical properties such as volume, density, surface area, pore diameter, etc... of 
              all structural files (.cif) in database directory automatically.
Usage: ./autocal.sh $path_database.cif
Output: 
	AUTOMAT.out1.dat: Properties for absorbent 
	AUTOMAT.out2.dat: Properties for absorbate as molecule 1, N2
	AUTOMAT.out3.dat: Properties for absorbate as molecule 2, C3H6

* screen.sh: Filter to satisfy specific conditions 
Usage: ./screen.sh
Output:
	SCREEN_TOTAL_in.dat
	SCREEN_out1.dat: Density Condition (> 2.0 g/cm3) 
	SCREEN_out2.dat: Surface Area Condition (> 400 m2/g)
	SCREEN_out3.dat: Accessibility Conditon (ASA/SA> 0.95; UnitCell & SuperCell)
	SCREEN_out4.dat: Pore Diameter Conditon (> 5.0 Angstroms)

* clean.sh: Waste all unnecessible files
Usage: ./clean.sh

